==English==

===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*(s)ker- (turn)}}
From {{bor|en|ML.|incarcerātus}}, past participle of {{m|la|incarcerō||to imprison}}, from {{der|en|la|in-||in}} + {{m|la|carcer||a prison}}, meaning "put behind lines (bars)" – Latin root is of a lattice or grid. Related to {{m|en|cancel||cross out with lines}} and {{m|en|chancel||area behind a lattice}}.

See also {{m|en|carcerate}} and {{m|en|cancer}}.

